You're done!

74
00:08:51,780 --> 00:08:53,820
Congratulations!

75
00:08:55,540 --> 00:08:56,600
By the way,

76
00:08:56,600 --> 00:08:59,200
did you know that the /ɔr/ sound

77
00:08:59,200 --> 00:09:03,760
is represented by several combinations of letters?

78
00:09:03,760 --> 00:09:05,540
Take a look:

79
00:09:05,540 --> 00:09:06,760
Most often,

80
00:09:06,760 --> 00:09:11,200
the /ɔr/ sound is represented by 'or'

81
00:09:11,200 --> 00:09:14,640
as in "sport" or "north."

82
00:09:14,640 --> 00:09:17,320
Less often by 'ar'

83
00:09:17,320 --> 00:09:20,480
as in "warm" or "quarter,"

84
00:09:20,480 --> 00:09:21,520
and

85
00:09:21,520 --> 00:09:26,040
'oar' as in "board" or "roar."

86
00:09:26,040 --> 00:09:29,060
There are quite a few words with 'our'

87
00:09:29,060 --> 00:09:32,320
as in "four' or "source,"

88
00:09:32,320 --> 00:09:34,460
and 'oor'

89
00:09:34,460 --> 00:09:37,940
as in "door" or "floor."

90
00:09:37,940 --> 00:09:40,380
And there are a couple of other variants,

91
00:09:40,380 --> 00:09:45,380
like in the words "horrible" and "warranty."

92
00:09:45,760 --> 00:09:48,320
While several of these combinations of letters

93
00:09:48,320 --> 00:09:52,000
represent the /ɔr/ sound in some words,

94
00:09:52,000 --> 00:09:57,520
they may also represent other R-colored vowels in other words.

95
00:09:57,520 --> 00:09:59,560
Yes, it's confusing,

96
00:09:59,560 --> 00:10:02,600
but you're used to it already, aren't you? :)

